{"actual_usd":0.15932000000000002,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":234,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31162,"reply":"\"Yeah, that’s exactly the pressure point.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the light’s catching on the well chain.* \"If Jesus is only an example, then the cross starts to look wasteful — tragic, maybe moving, but not necessary.\"\n\n\"The reason Christians say he had to die is that our problem isn’t just ignorance about how to love. It’s guilt, bondage, rebellion, death — the whole wreck of sin.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a little.* \"An example can instruct me. It can even inspire me. But it can’t forgive me, reconcile me to God, or break the power of sin on its own.\"\n\n\"So if Christ only lived beautifully, I’d admire him and still be stuck.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"The cross means he isn’t only saying, ‘Live like this.’ He’s doing something for us that we could not do for ourselves.\"\n\n\"Then the resurrection is the receipt that it worked.\" *I look back at you.* \"Do you want the short version of why that ‘for us’ has to involve death specifically?\"","rolling_24h_usd":51.86395500000003,"run_id":"d9921622-8020-4c8b-ad42-16d26f7f38dc"}
